answers.body_markdown:
The behavior is driven by `LiteralHandlingMode`, which has 3 settings:

**AUTO**&lt;br/&gt;
Criteria queries uses bind parameters for any literal that is not a numeric value.  This is the default behavior if configuration is not explicitly specified.

**BIND**&lt;br/&gt;
Used to increase the likelihood of JDBC statement caching, you might want to use bind parameters for numeric values too. The `BIND` mode will use bind variables for any literal value.

**INLINE**&lt;br/&gt;
mode will inline literal values as-is. To prevent SQL injection, never use `INLINE` with String variables. Always use constants with the `INLINE` mode.

To adjust the default setting, set `hibernate.criteria.literal_handling_mode` accordingly.

